  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates a cognitive behavioral therapy intervention for mothers with symptoms of
      anxiety and depression living in insecure environments using a randomized controlled
      methodology. Key outcomes of interest include maternal mental health and infant cognitive
      development. The intervention will be delivered by community mental health workers who will
      be trained to administer 8 to 12 cognitive behavioral therapy sessions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
